# How the Project Works

Step 1: User Inputs

The user enters:

• Number of subjects
• Subject names
• Number of chapters per subject
• Exam date

Example Input:

Physics — 5 chapters
Maths — 4 chapters
Programming — 3 chapters
Exam Date — 20 days later

---

Step 2: Calculation

The program calculates:

• Total chapters
• Days remaining until exam
• Study distribution across days

The system then distributes chapters evenly across available days.

---

Step 3: Study Plan Generation

The system generates:

• Date-wise study plan
• Subject-wise distribution
• Chapter allocation

Example Output:

Day 1 — Physics Chapter 1
Day 2 — Maths Chapter 1
Day 3 — Programming Chapter 1
Day 4 — Physics Chapter 2
Day 5 — Maths Chapter 2

---

Step 4: Data Visualization

The project also displays:

• Study plan table
• Progress bar chart
• Total chapters overview

This makes the plan easier to understand and follow.

